comments.body:
@TomSweeneyRedHat we have recently stumbled across this exact issue at a company I work for. We raised a ticket with RedHat support (04091735) but they struggled to understand our issue. We are using GitLab to execute scripts for billing processes etc which spawns a new container for each script execution, of which there are hundreds per day.

Because of all the GUID based exit files stored in /run/user/<uid>/libpod/persist we started running into issues where we exhausted the inode usage of the server and then our pipeline jobs fail - therefore assume the issue is directly related.

Any ideas which release of Podman this would be rolled up into? We were about to implement a temporary script to perform the cleanup.
